content:
HANLEY, Jeanene
Graduate student (since 1986) at University of Oklahoma in the Department of
Biochemistry and Molecular Biology. Working on the gene regulation of a
retinal protein in Drosophila. Recommended by Robert Broyles and Sara Tobin.
HIDALGO, Alicia
A Spanish national studying (since 1986) for a degree with the
Developmental Biology Unit of the Imperial Cancer Research Fund at Oxford
University. Working with the segment polarity gene "patched" in Drosophila.
Advisor: P.W. Ingham. 
JARZEM, Jacquelyn (Jackie)
A senior graduate student at the University of Texas (Austin) with Antone
Jacobson with whom she is finishing a thesis (for June of an
ultrastructural study (SEM) of the origin of the pronephric duct in chick
embryos. Highly recommended by Jacobson and Matt Winkler.
KELLY, Christopher
A graduate student since 1987 of the Committe on Evolutionary Biology at the
University of Chicago. Is interested in the developmental aspects of
evolution and wants to do a research thesis in that area. Recommended by
David Jablonski and Michael LaBarbera. It was felt that he would add
interesting diversity to the student group.
LANE, Mary
A student at University of Iowa (since 1982) in laboratory of Michael Solursh
where she has ben working on cell~matrix interactions during cell migration in
the sea urchin embryo. 
MATRANGA, Valeria
Dr. Matranga is a junior faculty member in the Department of Cellular and
Developmental Biology at the University of Palermo (Sicily). She is "The
Alberto Monroy Fellow" to the Embryology Course with funds provided by several
Italian foundations to encourage Italian students to study embryology at the
MBL. Highly recom ended by Giovanni Guidice in whose Department she works.
MAYOR, Roberto
A student in the cell biology program at the University of Chile in
Santiago since 1986. At present works with cytoskeleton in mouse embryos but
wished to learn about other developmental systems. Recommended by William
Jeffery and Joseph Sanger who taught him in a short workshop (the Cytoskeleton
and Developmental BiolOgY) in Santiago.
PECULIS, Brenda
A second year graduate student at Johns Hopkins, who will be doing her thesis
work with Joe Gall at the Carnegie Lab. Interested in gene control problems
in development; most of her previous background has been in molecular biology.
PESAVENTO, Patricia 
Second year graduate student at Harvard in the laboratory of Larry Goldstein.
Will be doing a thesis on microtubule associated proteins and the role of the
cytoskeleton in development.
